Perletto is a comune (municipality) in the Province of Cuneo in the Italian region Piedmont, located about 65.93 kilometres (40.97 mi) southeast of Turin and about 58.18 kilometres (36.15 mi) northeast of Cuneo.


== Geography ==
As of 31 December 2004, it had a population of 321 and an area of 10.5 square kilometres (4.1 sq mi). Perletto borders the following municipalities: Castino, Cortemilia, Olmo Gentile, San Giorgio Scarampi, Serole, and Vesime.


